"title": "5562: suffering, of the innocent",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5562",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture does not teach that the wicked will suffer, whereas the innocent and blameless will prosper. It offers insights into the place of suffering in the lives of the innocent, and the apparent injustice of this situation.</p>\n<h2>The apparent injustice of suffering</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:13\">HAB 1:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:7\">JOB 19:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:1\">JOB 24:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:12\">JOB 24:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps59:3-Ps59:4\">PSA 59:3–59:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:1\">PSA 74:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:11\">PSA 74:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps88:5\">PSA 88:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps88:14\">PSA 88:14</a></p>\n<h2>The wrong answers to suffering</h2>\n<p>The concept that those who suffer must be sinners:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job4:7\">JOB 4:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:2-John9:3\">JHN 9:2–9:3</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:25\">EZK 18:25</a> <em>the idea that God is unjust</em></p>\n<h2>The wrong reactions to suffering</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:9-Job2:10\">JOB 2:9–2:10</a> <em>resentment against God</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job23:13-Job23:15\">JOB 23:13–23:15</a> <em>being terrified of God</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job40:2\">JOB 40:2</a> <em>arguing with God</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:3\">PSA 73:3</a> <em>envying the wicked</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:13\">PSA 73:13</a> <em>disillusionment</em></p>\n<h2>The right reactions to suffering</h2>\n<h3>Reverent submission</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:21\">JOB 1:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job28:28\">JOB 28:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job34:12\">JOB 34:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job36:26\">JOB 36:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job37:19\">JOB 37:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job40:4\">JOB 40:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:40\">LAM 3:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:49-Lam3:50\">LAM 3:49–3:50</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:28\">MAT 10:28</a></p>\n<h3>Trust in God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:25\">GEN 18:25</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps55:22-Ps55:23\">PSA 55:22–55:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:23\">EXO 2:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps56:3-Ps56:4\">PSA 56:3–56:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps59:16\">PSA 59:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps62:5\">PSA 62:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps70:2\">PSA 70:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:6\">PSA 107:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:13\">PSA 107:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:19\">PSA 107:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:28\">PSA 107:28</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:50\">PSA 119:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:153\">PSA 119:153</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:17-Dan3:18\">DAN 3:17–3:18</a> <em>the trust shown by Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:17-Hab3:18\">HAB 3:17–3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:23\">1PE 2:23</a> <em>the example of Jesus Christ</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:19\">1PE 4:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:7\">1PE 5:7</a></p>\n<h2>God's reaction to suffering</h2>\n<h3>Concern for those who suffer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps9:12\">PSA 9:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:25\">EXO 2:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs14:26\">2KI 14:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:6\">PSA 1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:18-Ps33:19\">PSA 33:18–33:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:4\">JAS 5:4</a></p>\n<h3>Anger at the wicked</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps11:5\">PSA 11:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps59:8\">PSA 59:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:6-Ezek36:7\">EZK 36:6–36:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:9\">HAB 2:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:12\">HAB 2:12</a></p>\n<h2>God's response to suffering</h2>\n<h3>Deliverance for those who suffer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:19\">PSA 34:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:10-Job42:12\">JOB 42:10–42:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:16\">REV 7:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:4\">REV 21:4</a></p>\n<h3>Judgment for the wicked</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:5\">MAL 3:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:19-Exod3:20\">EXO 3:19–3:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:16-Ps73:18\">PSA 73:16–73:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps141:10\">PSA 141:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:3\">AMO 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:1\">NAM 3:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:19\">NAM 3:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:16\">HAB 2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:41-Matt25:46\">MAT 25:41–25:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:13\">JAS 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:18\">1PE 4:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:6-Rev18:7\">REV 18:6–18:7</a></p>",
